[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

12
00:00:25,793 --> 00:00:27,434
[SPEAKER_01]: So Kate and I talked a couple of weeks ago.

13
00:00:28,935 --> 00:00:30,977
[SPEAKER_01]: She has some pretty exciting projects in the works.

14
00:00:32,237 --> 00:00:34,779
[SPEAKER_01]: So yeah, if you want to talk a little bit about those, that'd be awesome.

15
00:00:35,119 --> 00:00:35,439
[SPEAKER_01]: Sure.

16
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:45,185
[SPEAKER_03]: So this year, our group has become fiscally sponsored by Fractured Atlas, so we can operate as a nonprofit.

17
00:00:45,286 --> 00:00:47,107
[SPEAKER_03]: And so we're going ahead with that.

18
00:00:47,127 --> 00:00:53,871
[SPEAKER_03]: And we have several programs that we're running with the Medford Housing Authority.

19
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:57,705
[SPEAKER_03]: And the one that I'm going to talk about today is called Just Flix Medford.

20
00:00:57,985 --> 00:00:58,386
[SPEAKER_03]: It's what?

21
00:00:58,566 --> 00:01:00,027
[SPEAKER_03]: Just Flix Medford.

22
00:01:00,788 --> 00:01:09,354
[SPEAKER_03]: And this is based off from, well, we are working with David Harris, who created this Just Flix program when he was at the Houston Institute.

23
00:01:09,954 --> 00:01:16,900
[SPEAKER_03]: And he collaborated with Bob Glover, who's an Emmy nominated producer.

24
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:20,462
[SPEAKER_03]: He's produced things for Sesame Street and a variety of other things.

25
00:01:20,602 --> 00:01:22,584
[SPEAKER_03]: But they have taken,

26
00:01:23,194 --> 00:01:29,457
[SPEAKER_03]: this concept of using social media and smartphones to try to empower communities of color.

27
00:01:29,918 --> 00:01:33,820
[SPEAKER_03]: And so they make three to five minute short films.

28
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:42,544
[SPEAKER_03]: And this year's cohort, we're working with 12 high school students from Medford that are recruited from the Medford Housing Authority.

29
00:01:43,965 --> 00:01:48,928
[SPEAKER_03]: And so they've been working, doing research for their topic.

30
00:01:49,702 --> 00:02:01,448
[SPEAKER_03]: creating a production plan for the video, and they are going to screen these across a few different sites in Medford.

31
00:02:02,229 --> 00:02:13,675
[SPEAKER_03]: So the project is funded by Mass Humanities in collaboration with the Medford Housing Authority, the library, and the Royal House and Slave Quarters Museum.

32
00:02:14,936 --> 00:02:18,838
[SPEAKER_03]: And so we'll have three separate screenings at each of those individual sites.

33
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:26,322
[SPEAKER_03]: And then we're working on one final screening at the Chevalier in the fall to winter.

34
00:02:26,582 --> 00:02:31,823
[SPEAKER_03]: And that one we're hoping to invite some of the neighboring communities.

35
00:02:31,903 --> 00:02:38,225
[SPEAKER_03]: So Arlington and Somerville, invite some high school students and the housing authority residents as well.

36
